This paper discusses the use of Time-Sensitive Networking (TSN) in robotics, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses communication standards and network protocols, which are relevant to computer networks (cs.NI) and systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the problems with traditional switched Ethernet networks, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.ET, and cs.SE.
